#4 FCC

The Refinery is made up of Refining Process Units. All of the process units use the same prevention program. The prevention program elements listed below are described in further detail in the Executive Summary:

- Process Safety Information;

- Process Hazard Analysis;

- Operating Procedures;

- Training;

- Mechanical Integrity;

- Management of Change;

- Pre-Startup Review;

- Compliance Audits;

- Incident Investigation;

- Employee Participation;

- Safe Work Practices, including Hot Work Permit;

- Contractors.



The primary purpose of Unit 4 FCC is to increases the overall yield from each barrel of crude oil. The FCC unit converts the lower-valued vacuum gas oils to higher valued products using a process combining catalytic reaction, heat and distillation.

