The primary purpose of Unit 5 FCC Gas Plant is to separate the gasoline from the olefins and the refinery fuel gas. The overhead naptha is first separated into vapor and liquid in the overhead accumulator. The vapor goes to the wet gas compressors, then on to the absorber/deethanizer. The liquid portion is further separated to remove sour water and is sent to Unit 35 Merox unit. This unit includes 19C-1 amine absorber.

